<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1120,1397]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,267,1120,1145]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Remarks.</emphasis>
This genus has been adequately described by Wang &amp; Zhang (2014) for the species collected from 
<collectingCountry box="[151,218,1156,1181]" name="China" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">China</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[280,383,1156,1181]" name="Thailand" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Thailand</collectingCountry>
. The genus can readily be recognised by the concave disc of the crown, transverse carina indistinct in fore part of crown, lateral carinae higher than median carina, male pygofer with long, slender ventral process exceeding posterodorsal margin; aedeagus with bilobed, lamellate dorsal apodeme arising from atrium and extended dorsolaterad, with lamellate ventral apophysis, shaft short, recurved dorsally, gonopore apical. Wang &amp; Zhang (2014) separated this genus from 
<taxonomicName box="[615,746,1300,1325]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Evacanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[615,746,1300,1325]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Evacanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the structure of the crown. The face is also distinctive in that the gena beneath the eye is strongly incurved (
<figureCitation box="[748,847,1336,1361]" captionStart="FIGURES 4" captionStartId="38.[151,264,1849,1872]" captionTargetBox="[219,1371,189,1800]" captionTargetId="figure@38.[169,1421,163,1832]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURES 4 A–V. Species of Evacanthini. A–J Habitus: A–B. Female Risefronta albicincta Wang &amp; Li (Distant).; C–D. Female Striatanus delta sp. nov.; E–F. Male Taperus indicus sp. nov.; G–H. Female Taperus sp.; I–J. Male Vangama steneosaura Distant. [A, C, E, G, I, dorsal views; B. D, F, H, J, lateral views]. K–V. Faces: K. Male Apphia flava sp. nov.; L. Bundera acutivertex sp. nov.; M.B. bambusana; N–O.Male and female Carinata midfasciana; P.Concavocorona kambaitisp. nov.; Q–R. Male and female Cunedda phaeops; S. Evacanthus albipennis sp. nov.; T. Evacanthus bellus; U. E. convolutus sp. nov.; V.E. distinctus sp. nov.." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1195894/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Fig. 4 P</figureCitation>
). One new species of this genus from 
<collectingCountry box="[1298,1407,1337,1361]" name="Myanmar" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Myanmar</collectingCountry>
is described below.
</paragraph>
